passages.text: Questions for management

Balance sheet. How do you think about managing a downside case in commodity markets? What are your latest thoughts on target net debt (circa \(\) 2.5- 3bn\(given\) < 2x EBITDA target)? How low does ND need to be before revisiting dividends / growth? It's clear the company isn't looking to raise equity, is this driven by an internal view on valuation per share that hasn't been met? What are the inorganic options to reduce debt referred to in the shareholders' letter?
Portfolio. Can you discuss whether any assets are actively being pursued for sale?

Onslow volumes. How have you managed to achieve 35Mtpa for 4 weeks while the road is being repaired? What does this suggest for sprint capacity post repair, particularly as transhipper 7 is commissioned in August? Do you expect product quality to remain consistent with recent quarters going forward? Will you look at more hedging?
Onslow haul road. How are the repair works going? When do you expect to avoid using public roads?

Autonomous Trucking: How is the transition to autonomous trucking likely to be implemented and what are the trigger points for getting this underway? What are the expected benefits once fully implemented?
Onslow trucking incident. What are the key issues that led to the latest incident? Is there a risk the regulator will impose conditions on how the road is operated if more issues occur?

Onslow iron ore sustaining capex. Can you discuss the low sustaining capex (A \(\) 4/t\(vs BHP/RIO/FMG (typically US\) 5/t+)- how does maintaining the road compare to rail? What are the key differences in maintaining the port & mine operations?

Pilbara Hub. Can you discuss how quickly the Lambs Creek project can be executed and what the expected cost impact is from getting this up and running? What is the production scope? Do you expect to convert the 161Mt resources into reserves? What are the key drivers for the elevated costs of around \(\) 75- 80/t?

Lithium - Marion. How sustainable is the drop in costs at Marion? It appears this relates to lower material movements - can you discuss if / when strip ratio rises again at Marion? When does ore mining occur from underground, and what will be the cost impact? What proportion of ore feed will come from underground?

Lithium - Wodgina. Is it a lower strip ratio that's driving lower costs at Wodgina? Again, how sustainable is this? Why not run 3 trains now that prices have improved given this would help the balance sheet and the resource remains open? What has driven the improved outlook for recoveries?
MIN.AX, MIN AU Price (28 Aug 25):A \(\) 36.87\$ Price Target (Jun- 26):A \(\) 26.00\$

- Lithium - Bald Hill. It was mentioned on the call that \(\) 1,500\(/t is a price objective to revisit growth in lithium, how long would you need to see this for?- Mining Services Volume. It appears third-party volumes are falling in FY26 given the mid-point of guidance and the benefit from Onslow volumes, what is driving this? It appears the margin is falling slightly from\) \ \(2.2 / t\) to \(\) 2/t\(this year, what is driving this reduction? The quarterly run rate in volumes for FY26 is below the 4Q25 rate, why is there so much volatility quarter to quarter?- Capex. It appears stay in business spend is around\) \ \(500 - 600m\) , what are the key items that could impact FY27? How much are you targeting to reduce FY27 from \(\) 1.1bn\(in FY26?- Energy Division. There is still capex going into this, are there opportunities to generate value near-term other than the potential contingent payment from Hancock?- ESG, Succession planning. Can you discuss some of the key priorities?
Mineral Resources Ltd. (Underweight; Price Target: A\(26.00)

Mineral Resources is an ASX- listed company focused on contractor crushing, mining services, iron ore, lithium and gas operations. MIN has crushing contracts with some of the world's largest mining companies in iron ore, gold and lithium operations, as well as its own operating assets. While the crushing business (CSI) has been the long- term core business, MIN has unlocked value in its lithium assets, Mt. Marion, and Wodgina (Bald Hill on care and maintenance). MIN is also ramping up production at its iron ore assets via the Onslow project. We have an Underweight rating on the stock based on valuation.
Our Jun- 26 price target is set at our DCF valuation (rounded off to the nearest dollar).
